records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dyresha Shavonda Lawrence in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Latoya B.  Defendant sentenced to serve 3 months in the House of Correction with credit for 1 day time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.
Conditions:  
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $853.00 to Latoya B. or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  No contact with Latoya B.;
*  Court will waive any costs and surcharges that can be waived; all mandatory costs and surcharges are to be paid during the term of probation;
*  Defendant to submit DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;

If the defendant pays restitution and commits no new violations, Court will allow probation to be terminated after 6 months.
